{# Port-wiring snippet for Rust / Axum backends.

Renders the ``pub mod ports;`` module declaration + adapter ``use``
lines + Axum state wiring, intended for the
``FORGE:LIB_MOD_REGISTRATION`` anchor in ``src/lib.rs`` — the same
anchor queue_port already wires to. Axum ``Router::with_state`` and
``.layer(Extension(...))`` wiring lands through ``service_factory``;
this macro emits the module + use scaffolding around it.

Spec context (``port``) — every field is required:
  - name              — snake_case identifier (e.g. ``llm``, ``queue``)
  - interface_path    — Rust module path of the Port trait. Two
                        shapes accepted:
                          * ``src/ports/llm.rs`` — the macro derives
                            the parent ``ports`` module decl from the
                            second-to-last segment.
                          * ``crate::ports::llm`` — used verbatim in
                            the ``use`` statement; no derivation.
  - adapter_imports   — tuple of ``use``-target paths
                        (e.g. ``crate::adapters::llm_openai::OpenAiAdapter``).
                        Each becomes one ``use <path>;`` line.
  - service_factory   — the wiring statement(s). Verbatim. Typically
                        an ``Extension(Arc::new(<Adapter>::new(...)))``
                        layer registration or an ``AppState`` field
                        assignment. Multiline OK.
#}
{%- macro snippet(port) -%}
// Port: {{ port.name }}
{%- if port.interface_path.startswith('crate::') or '::' in port.interface_path %}
use {{ port.interface_path }}::*;
{%- else %}
{%- set _segments = port.interface_path
    | replace('.rs', '')
    | replace('src/', '')
    | replace('\\', '/')
    | replace('/', '::') %}
pub mod {{ _segments.rsplit('::', 1)[0] }};
use crate::{{ _segments }}::*;
{%- endif %}
{% for imp in port.adapter_imports -%}
use {{ imp }};
{% endfor -%}
{{ port.service_factory }}
{%- endmacro %}
